reviewText: Arrived as advertised.  Early Wayne B movies were a hoot.  Poor old Roy is dated.  Lone Ranger series brought back fond memories.  Lots of shows for those who are collectors and those who are in the age range of 55-80 yrs.  Most are rare to see in this day of action and gore movies.  Better times in the late 30's to mid-1950's for Western Heroes.  "Cowboy Sunset" videos is the best way to describe this huge compilation.
Just delighted to have such a rare treat in my collection. Hours of anticipation. Now I need to save for a Power Converter for my Region One player.
Gave as a gift to my father and have gotten no complaints.

This is not really a review. It is merely a listing of the contents of this DVD collection. At the time that I typed this, Amazon had not yet provided one. This DVD is made up of mostly B Western movies, episodes of Western TV shows, and a fifteen chapter Western serial. I hope this listing is useful.
